+const summaryLines = [];
+summaryLines.push('Analysis summary for ds001_breast');
+summaryLines.push('');
+summaryLines.push(`Cohort: 50,000 patients. Outcome was pfs_months (mean ${fmt(pfsMean)}, SD ${fmt(pfsSd)}, quartiles ${pfsQ.slice(1, 4).map((x) => fmt(x)).join('/')} months). I used OLS models on the natural month scale with signed coefficients; primary adjusted models included age_years, sex_female, ecog_ps, stage_iv, metastatic sites, node_positive, breast cancer biomarkers, ki67_pct, tumor_size_cm, albumin_g_dl, ldh_u_l, weight_loss_pct_6mo, crp_mg_l, nlr, and all treatment indicators.`);
+summaryLines.push('');
+summaryLines.push('Treatment main effects and biomarker heterogeneity:');
+summaryLines.push(`- Trastuzumab had a positive adjusted main association (${fmt(c('treatment_trastuzumab').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_trastuzumab').p)}), and its benefit was strongly concentrated in HER2-defined disease: interaction with her2_positive ${fmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_positive.interaction.beta)} months (p=${pFmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_positive.interaction.p)}) and with her2_amplification ${fmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_amplification.interaction.beta)} months (p=${pFmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_amplification.interaction.p)}). The interaction with her2_low was ${fmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_low.interaction.beta)} months (p=${pFmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_low.interaction.p)}), which did not support the hypothesis that HER2-low patients derive a comparable or larger trastuzumab association.`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Palbociclib was positively associated with PFS (${fmt(c('treatment_palbociclib').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_palbociclib').p)}). Its interaction with er_positive was ${fmt(interactions.palbociclib_er_positive.interaction.beta)} months (p=${pFmt(interactions.palbociclib_er_positive.interaction.p)}) and with pr_positive ${fmt(interactions.palbociclib_pr_positive.interaction.beta)} months (p=${pFmt(interactions.palbociclib_pr_positive.interaction.p)}), supporting hormone-receptor subgroup heterogeneity.`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Tamoxifen showed a positive adjusted association (${fmt(c('treatment_tamoxifen').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_tamoxifen').p)}), with a further ER-positive interaction of ${fmt(interactions.tamoxifen_er_positive.interaction.beta)} months (p=${pFmt(interactions.tamoxifen_er_positive.interaction.p)}).`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Olaparib had a positive adjusted main association (${fmt(c('treatment_olaparib').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_olaparib').p)}). Interactions were positive for brca1_mutation (${fmt(interactions.olaparib_brca1.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.olaparib_brca1.interaction.p)}) and brca2_mutation (${fmt(interactions.olaparib_brca2.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.olaparib_brca2.interaction.p)}), supporting BRCA-specific treatment heterogeneity.`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Pembrolizumab was positively associated with PFS (${fmt(c('treatment_pembrolizumab').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_pembrolizumab').p)}). Autoimmune disease modified this weakly/non-significantly (${fmt(interactions.pembrolizumab_autoimmune.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.pembrolizumab_autoimmune.interaction.p)}), while higher NLR significantly attenuated the association (${fmt(interactions.pembrolizumab_nlr.interaction.beta)} months per SD NLR, p=${pFmt(interactions.pembrolizumab_nlr.interaction.p)}).`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Sacituzumab govitecan was negatively associated with PFS after adjustment (${fmt(c('treatment_sacituzumab_govitecan').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_sacituzumab_govitecan').p)}). Stage IV and liver metastasis did not add strong negative interaction evidence (stage IV interaction ${fmt(interactions.sacituzumab_stage_iv.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.sacituzumab_stage_iv.interaction.p)}; liver metastasis interaction ${fmt(interactions.sacituzumab_liver_mets.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.sacituzumab_liver_mets.interaction.p)}), suggesting the adverse main association was not confined to those subgroups in this model.`);
+summaryLines.push('');
