+summaryLines.push(`- Trastuzumab hypotheses were not supported. The adjusted main coefficient was ${fmt(c('treatment_trastuzumab').beta)} months (p=${pFmt(c('treatment_trastuzumab').p)}), and interactions with her2_positive (${fmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_positive.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_positive.interaction.p)}), her2_amplification (${fmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_amplification.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_amplification.interaction.p)}), and her2_low (${fmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_low.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.trastuzumab_her2_low.interaction.p)}) were all small and non-significant.`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Tamoxifen also lacked an adjusted benefit (${fmt(c('treatment_tamoxifen').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_tamoxifen').p)}), and its ER-positive interaction was small/non-significant (${fmt(interactions.tamoxifen_er_positive.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.tamoxifen_er_positive.interaction.p)}).`);
+summaryLines.push(`- Olaparib was not significantly associated with longer PFS after adjustment (${fmt(c('treatment_olaparib').beta)} months, p=${pFmt(c('treatment_olaparib').p)}). BRCA1 and BRCA2 interaction hypotheses were not supported (BRCA1 ${fmt(interactions.olaparib_brca1.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.olaparib_brca1.interaction.p)}; BRCA2 ${fmt(interactions.olaparib_brca2.interaction.beta)} months, p=${pFmt(interactions.olaparib_brca2.interaction.p)}).`);
